HEADWORD: Natch
<hw>Natch</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧ch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>nache</ets> fesse, LL. <ets>natica</ets>, from L. <ets>natis</ets>
the rump, buttocks. Cf. <er>Aitchbone</er>.]</ety> <def>The rump of
beef; esp., the lower and back part of the rump.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Natch bone</b></col>, <cd>the edgebone, or aitchbone, in
beef.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Natchez</ent>⟦br⟧
